false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27214"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause oneself to be clean, to make oneself purified, to remove impurities from oneself","tags":["intransitive","reflexive"],"examples":[{"text":"وَإِنْ كُنْتُمْ جُنُبًا فَٱطَّهَّرُوا","english":"And if ye are unclean, purify yourselves."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to clear up, to end or be removed, to have a body free from its effects, to recover"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَطَهَّرَ (taṭahhara) (form V)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27214","headword_ar":"تطهّر","root":"Thr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTah~urN","text_ar":"تَطَهُّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is sometimes changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiT~ah~ara","text_ar":"اِطَّهَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiT~ah~urN","text_ar":"اِطَّهُّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"being incorporated into the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"T","text_ar":"ط"},{"kind":"text","text":", and this requiring a conjunctive"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sgh, K,) in order that the word may not begin with a quiescent letter: (Sgh:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TahuwrN","text_ar":"طَهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also an inf. n. [or rather a quasi-inf. n.] (Sb, K) of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTah~ara","text_ar":"تَطَهَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, TA,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDuwo'N","text_ar":"وَضُوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [said to be] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawaD~aA^a","text_ar":"تَوَضَّاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The meaning is, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became cleansed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purified:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cleansed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purified, himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he washed himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tTh~r biAlmaA='i","text_ar":"تطهّر بِالمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cleansed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"washed, himself with water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he performed the ablution termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwuDuwo'","text_ar":"الوُضُوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAisotinojaA='","text_ar":"الاِسْتِنْجَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tTh~r","text_ar":"تطهّر"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, as used in the Kur ix. 109: (Mgh, TA:) and the same verb, alone, is expl. as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made use of water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what supplied its place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus used in the Kur v. 9. (TA.) In the Kur vii. 80 and xxvii. 57, the verb is used derisively. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tTh~rt","text_ar":"تطهّرت"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiT~ah~arato","text_ar":"اِطَّهَّرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She cleansed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purified, herself by washing, from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pollution of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the menstrual discharge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"&c."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taharato","text_ar":"طَهَرَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tahurato","text_ar":"طَهُرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, * K;) agreeably with what is said in the B, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tahara","text_ar":"طَهَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tahura","text_ar":"طَهُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AT~h~r","text_ar":"اطّهّر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tTh~r","text_ar":"تطهّر"},{"kind":"text","text":"have the same signification: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tTh~rt","text_ar":"تطهّرت"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AT~h~rt","text_ar":"اطّهّرت"},{"kind":"text","text":"have this signification; but the unaugmented verb has the signification first assigned to it, or “ her discharge of blood stopped: ” (Abu-l-'Abbás, IAar:) in the Kur ii. 222, some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY yaTohurona","text_ar":"حَتَّى يَطْهُرْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and others,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY yaT~ah~arona","text_ar":"حَتَّى يَطَّهَّرْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the latter reading is the preferable, on account of the difference between the two forms of the verb, just mentioned: (Abu-l-'Abbás:) or the law which allows not the touching a woman until she has performed the ablution mentioned above shows the two forms of the verb to be the same in signification. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed himself far from unclean things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impurities."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K. *) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He refrained from sin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and from what was not good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he removed himself far from low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignoble, habits:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in this sense, accord. to some, it is used in the Kur vii. 80 and xxvii. 57. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tTh~r mina AlA_ivomi","text_ar":"تطهّر مِنَ الاـِثْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed himself far from sin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"}],"source_refs":["Sgh","K","Sb","Mgh","TA","S","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}